<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Warrior vs Spellcaster on PvP</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Madman at Large">Madman at Large</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 1:58 p.m. 14/3/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Warrior vs Spellcaster on PvP<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR></STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>Was afraid that the PvP server was going to be flooded with juveniles, but, to my suprise in general the players where mature and civil. Beacause of the limited time I got on the server I didn't get to experiment with that many different classes in player vs. player combat. Let's talk in the limited scope of 1 vs. 1. Isn't root essential? Damn if I didn't have a hell of a time running little backstabbers down with my shadow knight! It seems that spellcasting is essential for successfull PvP combat. Please share with me your experiences, and, if you dont mind, your race/class choice for the final.

<P>My current thoughts are:
<BR>1. HUMAN NECROMANCER
<BR>2. HALF-ELF RANGER ( QUICK ADVANCEMENT FROM TRACKING)
<BR>3. HUMAN MONK (EASY TO BOUNCE BACK FROM A BAD FIGHT)
<BR>4. TROLL SHAMAN (ROOT)
<BR>5. EURODITE WIZARD
<P>Are dark-elves viable to travel the world with? Will my friends be constantly groaning over taking the long route? Do RANGER/PALIDIN/SHADOW-KNIGHTS ever get higher than 3rd circle spells? Do any get bind? What are YOU going to play, and WHY?
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
